# Copy to `.env` for local dev. Restart `npm run dev` after changes.
#
# --- GitHub Actions (production build / Pages deploy) ---
# Repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
#
# Repository secrets (recommended names):
#   VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID   OAuth Web client ID from Google Cloud Console
# Optional alias GitHub also accepts:
#   GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID        used if VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID is not set
#
# Repository variable (non-secret) OR secret:
#   VITE_API_URL            Public production API base URL (e.g. https://api.example.com)
# The deploy workflow writes these into `.env` on the runner, then runs `npm run build`.
# PUBLIC_BASE_PATH is set only in CI (/pillweb); omit locally unless testing a Pages build.

VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
